.TH CHECKSUMS 1 "March 2026" "checksums 6.1.0" "User Commands"
.\"
.SH NAME
checksums \- generate and verify per\-file integrity metadata
.\"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B checksums
.RI [ options ]
.I DIRECTORY
.br
.B checksums
.B \-c
.I FILE
.RI [ \-a
.IR ALGO ]
.RI [ \-p
.IR N ]
.RI [ \-q ]
.RI [ DIRECTORY ]
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B checksums
generates and verifies per\-file integrity metadata using sidecar files.
For each directory under
.IR DIRECTORY ,
it computes per\-file checksums (md5, sha1, sha224, sha256, sha384, or sha512)
and writes them to a manifest file whose extension matches the algorithm
(e.g.\&
.IR .md5 ,
.IR .sha256 ).
Rich metadata (inode, device, mtime, size, hash) is stored in a companion
.I .meta
file, and a run log tracks each operation.
.PP
On subsequent runs,
.B checksums
compares stored metadata against disk state (inode, device, mtime, size) and
only rehashes files that have changed, providing fast incremental updates.
File replacements that preserve mtime and size are detected via inode changes.
.PP
By default, the tool uses md5 for per\-file hashes and sha256 for meta
signatures.
Sidecar files are named with a configurable base name (default:
.BR #####checksums##### )
and placed alongside the data files, or in a central store directory when
.B \-\-store\-dir
is used.
.PP
Running
.RB \(lq checksums
.IR DIRECTORY \(rq
with no options will:
.IP \(bu 2
Use md5 for per\-file hashes and sha256 for meta signatures.
.IP \(bu 2
Create sidecar files:
.IR #####checksums#####.md5 ,
.IR #####checksums#####.meta ,
.IR #####checksums#####.log .
.IP \(bu 2
Skip empty or container\-only directories.
.IP \(bu 2
Keep the root DIRECTORY clean (no sidecar files in root).
.IP \(bu 2
Reuse existing hashes when files are unchanged.
.IP \(bu 2
Run single\-threaded (PARALLEL_JOBS=1).
.IP \(bu 2
Prompt for confirmation before processing.
.IP \(bu 2
Write a run log:
.IR #####checksums#####.run.log .
.\"
.SH OPTIONS
.SS General Options
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-config " FILE"
Load configuration from
.I FILE
(overrides default config lookup).
.TP
.BR \-\-menu ", " \-\-interactive
Launch an interactive guided command builder.
Walks through all options step\-by\-step and displays the full command
for copy/paste or immediate execution.
Requires a TTY (not available in non\-interactive shells).
Combine with other flags to pre\-set defaults
(e.g.\&
.BR \-\-menu " " \-a " sha256" ).
.\"
.SS File Naming Options
.TP
.BI \-f " NAME" "\fR,\fB \-\-base\-name " NAME
Base name for sidecar files (.md5/.meta/.log).
Default:
.BR #####checksums##### .
.TP
.BI \-l " LOGNAME" "\fR,\fB \-\-log\-base " LOGNAME
Log base name.
Default: same as
.BR \-f .
.TP
.BI \-D " DIR" "\fR,\fB \-\-store\-dir " DIR
Store all sidecar files in
.I DIR
using a mirror tree layout.
Keeps source directories clean;
.I DIR
is created if needed.
Migrates existing scattered sidefiles on first use.
.\"
.SS Hashing Options
.TP
.BI \-a " ALGO" "\fR,\fB \-\-per\-file\-algo " ALGO
Per\-file checksum algorithm.
Default:
.BR md5 .
Supported:
.BR md5 ,
.BR sha1 ,
.BR sha224 ,
.BR sha256 ,
.BR sha384 ,
.BR sha512 .
The manifest file extension matches the algorithm.
Comma\-separated for multi\-algo:
.BR "\-a md5,sha256" .
Writes one manifest per algorithm in a single pass.
Incompatible with
.BR \-\-check ,
.BR \-\-status ,
.BR \-\-verify\-only .
.TP
.BI \-m " ALGO" "\fR,\fB \-\-meta\-sig " ALGO
Meta signature algorithm:
.B sha256
(default),
.BR md5 ,
or
.BR none .
.TP
.BR \-R ", " \-\-no\-reuse
Disable reuse heuristics; force rehash of all files.
Use with
.B \-r
for a full forced rebuild.
.TP
.BI \-p " N" "\fR,\fB \-\-parallel " N
Number of parallel hashing/verification jobs.
Default:
.BR 1 .
Accepts: integer,
.B auto
(all cores), or fraction (3/4, 1/2, etc.).
.TP
.BI \-P " N" "\fR,\fB \-\-parallel\-dirs " N
Number of directories to process in parallel.
Default:
.BR 1 .
Accepts: integer,
.B auto
(all cores), or fraction (3/4, 1/2, etc.).
When > 1,
.B \-p
controls the shared worker pool across all directories.
.TP
.BI \-b " RULES" "\fR,\fB \-\-batch " RULES
Adaptive batching rules.
Default:
.BR \(dq0\-10M:20,10M\-40M:20,>40M:5\(dq .
Format:
.B LOW\-HIGH:COUNT,>HIGH:COUNT
with K/M/G suffixes.
.\"
.SS Run Control Options
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Dry\-run mode (no writes).
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Increase debug verbosity (repeatable).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase verbosity (repeatable).
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-force\-rebuild
Force rebuild (ignore existing manifests).
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-assume\-yes
Assume \(lqyes\(rq for all prompts (non\-interactive).
.TP
.B \-\-assume\-no
Assume \(lqno\(rq for all prompts (non\-interactive).
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress all output except errors.
.TP
.BR \-Q ", " \-\-no\-progress
Disable live progress reporting (default: on for TTY).
.TP
.BR \-M ", " \-\-minimal
Hash\-only mode: write .md5 manifest only, skip .meta/.log.
No first\-run logic, no meta signatures, no run log.
.\"
.SS First\-run Options
.TP
.BR \-F ", " \-\-first\-run
Bootstrap mode: verify existing .md5 files lacking .meta/.log.
.TP
.BI \-C " CHOICE" "\fR,\fB \-\-first\-run\-choice " CHOICE
First\-run choice:
.BR skip ,
.BR overwrite ,
or
.B prompt
(default).
.TP
.BR \-K ", " \-\-first\-run\-keep
Keep the first\-run log after overwrites (audit trail).
Default: delete stale first\-run log post\-overwrite.
.PP
Environment:
.B FIRST_RUN_KEEP=1
is equivalent to
.BR \-\-first\-run\-keep .
.\"
.SS Verification Options
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-verify\-only
Audit mode (no writes).
.TP
.BI \-c " FILE" "\fR,\fB \-\-check " FILE
Verify files against an external manifest
.IR FILE .
Compatible with
.BR md5sum\~\-c " / " sha256sum\~\-c .
Auto\-detects algorithm from file extension
.RI ( .md5 ,
.IR .sha256 ,
etc.).
Use
.BI \-a " ALGO"
to override.
An optional
.I DIRECTORY
argument sets the base path for relative filenames in the manifest.
Exits 0 if all entries verify, 1 if any failure.
Use
.B \-q
to suppress OK lines (show only failures).
Use
.BI \-p " N"
for parallel verification.
.TP
.BR \-z ", " \-\-no\-md5\-details
Disable per\-directory md5 verification in planning.
.TP
.B \-\-md5\-details
Enable md5 verification in planning (default).
.\"
.SS Status Options
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-status
Show what changed since the last manifest (diff mode).
Reads .md5/.meta manifests and compares against disk state.
Exits 0 if nothing changed, 1 if changes found.
Use with
.B \-R
to rehash and confirm changes (slower).
.\"
.SS Directory Handling Options
.TP
.B \-\-skip\-empty
Skip directories with no files (default).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-skip\-empty
Process empty or container\-only directories too.
.TP
.B \-\-allow\-root\-sidefiles
Allow sidecar files (.md5/.meta/.log) in root
.IR DIRECTORY .
Default: root sidefiles disabled.
.TP
.BR \-L ", " \-\-follow\-symlinks
Follow symbolic links when scanning directories and files.
By default, symlinks are not followed (safer, avoids loops).
When enabled, symlinks to files are included in manifests and symlinks
to directories are descended into.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-follow\-symlinks
Do not follow symbolic links (default).
.\"
.SS File Filtering Options
.TP
.BI \-e " PATTERN" "\fR,\fB \-\-exclude " PATTERN
Exclude files matching
.I PATTERN
(basename glob, repeatable).
Supports comma\-separated values:
.BR "\-\-exclude \(aq*.tmp,*.bak\(aq" .
.TP
.BI \-i " PATTERN" "\fR,\fB \-\-include " PATTERN
Include only files matching
.I PATTERN
(basename glob, repeatable).
Supports comma\-separated values:
.BR "\-\-include \(aq*.txt,*.md\(aq" .
If set, only matching files are processed (allowlist).
.TP
.BI \-\-max\-size " SIZE"
Skip files larger than
.I SIZE
(e.g., 10M, 1G, 500K).
.TP
.BI \-\-min\-size " SIZE"
Skip files smaller than
.I SIZE
(e.g., 1K, 100).
.\"
.SS Logging Options
.TP
.BI \-o " FORMAT" "\fR,\fB \-\-output " FORMAT
Log format:
.B text
(default),
.BR json ,
.BR csv .
.\"
.SH CONFIGURATION
By default,
.B checksums
looks for a configuration file named
.BI < BASE_NAME > .conf
in the root
.IR DIRECTORY .
With the default base name, this is
.IR #####checksums#####.conf .
Use
.BI \-\-config " FILE"
to specify an alternate path.
.PP
The configuration file uses a simple
.B key=value
format (one per line).
Comments (lines starting with
.BR # )
and blank lines are ignored.
Quoting of values is optional and stripped if present.
CLI arguments always override configuration file settings.
.PP
See
.I example/checksums.conf
for a complete template with all supported keys.
.\"
.SH PATTERNS
The
.B \-e
/
.B \-\-exclude
and
.B \-i
/
.B \-\-include
flags accept basename shell globs (e.g.,
.BR "*.tmp" ).
Both flags are repeatable and support comma\-separated values.
.PP
If include patterns are set, only matching files are processed (allowlist).
Exclude patterns always take precedence over include patterns.
.PP
Configuration file equivalents:
.B EXCLUDE_PATTERNS
and
.B INCLUDE_PATTERNS
(comma\-separated).
.\"
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS First\-run Bootstrap
Initialize meta/logs from existing .md5 files:
.PP
.EX
checksums \-F \-C overwrite \-a md5 \-m sha256 \-p 4 \\
    \-\-md5\-details \-\-skip\-empty /data/project
.EE
.PP
Verifies existing .md5 manifests that lack .meta/.log, recomputes mismatches,
and produces a first\-run log.
.\"
.SS Verify\-only Audit
Check integrity without writing anything:
.PP
.EX
checksums \-V \-a md5 \-m sha256 \-p 4 \-\-md5\-details \\
    \-\-skip\-empty \-\-assume\-yes /data/project
.EE
.PP
Reads existing manifests and reports VERIFIED, MISMATCH, or MISSING per file.
Ideal for CI/CD pipelines or scheduled audits.
.\"
.SS Dry\-run Planning
Preview what would happen without changes:
.PP
.EX
checksums \-n \-a sha256 \-m sha256 \-p 4 \-v \\
    \-\-md5\-details \-\-skip\-empty \-\-assume\-yes /data/project
.EE
.PP
Simulates all steps without writing sidecars.
Perfect for validating config files, exclude/include patterns, and batch rules.
.\"
.SS Status/Diff Check
Show what changed since last manifest:
.PP
.EX
checksums \-S \-\-skip\-empty /data/project
.EE
.PP
Read\-only diff mode.
Exits 0 if clean, 1 if changes exist (CI\-friendly).
Add
.B \-R
to rehash and confirm changes.
.\"
.SS Multi\-Algorithm Single Pass
Generate both .md5 and .sha256 manifests in one run:
.PP
.EX
checksums \-a md5,sha256 \-y /data/project
.EE
.PP
Each file is hashed once per algorithm (OS page cache amortizes re\-reads).
Writes one manifest file per algorithm.
Meta (.meta) stores only the primary (first) algorithm's hash.
.\"
.SS External Manifest Verification
Verify files against a sha256sum\-compatible manifest:
.PP
.EX
checksums \-c checksums.sha256 \-p 4 /data/project
.EE
.PP
Algorithm auto\-detected from extension.
Supports both GNU format
.RI ( "hash\~\~filename" )
and BSD format
.RI ( "ALGO (file) = hash" ).
Use
.B \-q
for quiet mode (failures only).
.\"
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
Also returned for user abort,
.BR \-\-help ,
.BR \-\-version ,
and
.BR \-\-assume\-no .
.TP
.B 1
Error (validation failure, runtime error, missing tools).
Also: changes found in
.B \-\-status
mode; check failures in
.B \-\-check
mode.
.TP
.B 2
Missing prerequisite (library files not found at startup).
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted (SIGINT / Ctrl\-C).
.TP
.B 143
Terminated (SIGTERM).
.\"
.SH FILES
.TP
.IB BASE_NAME .md5 "\fR, \fI.sha256\fR, etc."
Per\-file checksum manifest.
Extension matches the algorithm set by
.BR \-a .
Default base name:
.BR #####checksums##### .
.TP
.IB BASE_NAME .meta
Rich metadata file (inode, device, mtime, size, hash per file, meta signature).
.TP
.IB BASE_NAME .log
Per\-directory run log (append\-mode).
.TP
.IB BASE_NAME .run.log
Top\-level run log for the entire invocation.
.TP
.IB BASE_NAME .first\-run.log
First\-run verification log (created by
.BR \-F ).
.TP
.IB BASE_NAME .conf
Configuration file (looked up in root DIRECTORY by default).
.TP
.I PREFIX/share/bash\-completion/completions/checksums
Bash tab\-completion script (installed by
.BR "make install" ).
.TP
.I PREFIX/share/zsh/site\-functions/_checksums
Zsh tab\-completion script (installed by
.BR "make install" ).
.\"
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.B checksums
requires
.B Bash 4.0
or later.
Stock macOS ships Bash 3.2; install a newer version via:
.PP
.EX
brew install bash
.EE
.\"
